parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intermittent stalling of the engine can cause a loss of control, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities, especially when it occurs in heavy traffic or during deceleration.
symptoms: The engine stops or stalls while driving
usually at low speeds (10-15 mph)
during deceleration
or when downshifting
often accompanied by a drop in RPM below normal idle speed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the idle air control valve can cause the engine to stall, especially when idling or decelerating, which can lead to accidents or near-miss situations, particularly in heavy traffic.
symptoms: The engine stalls frequently
especially when idling or decelerating
the engine stalls at stop signs or red lights
the engine stalls when waiting in traffic
the rear lights may turn off when the engine stalls
the engine may stall repeatedly in a short period.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Stalling and Loss of Power in Hot Weather
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine stalling and loss of power in hot weather can cause the vehicle to become stranded, increasing the risk of accidents or injuries, especially when stuck in traffic or on a hot day.
symptoms: The engine stalls after being in steady cruise for an extended period
stalls repeatedly in very hot weather
fails to restart or has difficulty restarting
responds poorly to throttle opening
revs only up to 2000-3000 RPM
bogs down when throttle is opened further
and may die after starting and running for a short period (10-15 seconds).

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The fracture of the gear shift can cause the motorcycle to become stuck in gear, making it difficult or impossible to shift, which can lead to accidents or leave the rider stranded.
symptoms: The gear shift breaks or fractures
the motorcycle is unable to shift gears
the motorcycle becomes stuck in gear.
